<Layout title="Business Broker Mortgages · Florida M&amp;A Intermediary Chapter 475 Part I + IBBA + Lehman Scale &mdash; Deal Cycle Commission Qualifying" description="Florida business broker mortgage sub-page covering five practice categories under Florida Statutes Chapter 475 Part I regulated by Florida Real Estate Commission FREC under DBPR: main street business broker focused on $1M-$10M EV transactions across restaurants plus retail plus service businesses plus light industrial plus B2B services with commission structure typical 8-10% of EV at close plus deal cycle 6-12 months plus SBA 7(a) financing coordination; lower middle market M&A advisor focused on $10M-$100M EV transactions with sophisticated buyer pool strategic acquirers plus PE plus family offices plus independent sponsors plus search funds with Lehman scale commission 5% first $1M plus 4% second plus 3% third plus 2% fourth plus 1% above $4M plus retainer $25K-$100K plus success fee hybrid plus deal cycle 8-18 months; boutique M&A advisor / sell-side specialist focused on sector specialty healthcare M&A plus technology M&A plus services M&A plus distribution M&A plus professional services with deeper buyer relationships plus higher per-deal fees plus sometimes equity participation; franchise + service business specialist focused on restaurants plus franchises plus home services plus light industrial plus B2B services with specialty buyer networks plus franchisor relationships plus multi-unit operator pipeline; affiliated business broker operating under master broker-of-record license at Murphy Business plus Sunbelt Business Brokers plus Transworld Business Advisors plus VR Business Brokers FL franchisees plus boutique FL firms with split commission economics plus brokerage E&O coverage plus back office support. Florida business brokerage requires real estate licensing under Chapter 475 Part I sales associate or broker level plus 60-hour pre-license plus state exam plus 45-hour post-license plus ongoing 14-hour CE per 2-year cycle. IBBA International Business Brokers Association primary professional framework for main street plus lower middle market business brokers with CBI Certified Business Intermediary designation. M&A Source professional framework for lower middle market plus sophisticated M&A intermediaries with M&AMI Merger & Acquisition Master Intermediary designation. Florida Business Brokers Association state-level community. Deal cycle 6-18 months engagement-to-close typical with feast-or-famine commission pattern plus episodic large commission events plus heavy upfront investment in business valuation work plus marketing materials plus buyer outreach plus due diligence support typical $5K-$25K upfront sunk cost per engagement plus multi-month commission lag between deal close plus commission payment plus tax recognition. Co-brokerage splits when working with cooperating broker typical 50/50 split. Florida Sun Belt M&A activity substantial 2020-2026 driven by baby boomer business owner retirement wave plus business demographic transition plus Sun Belt corporate relocations plus Latin American business hub activity plus private equity roll-up activity plus ETA / search fund acquisition pipeline plus Florida small business density rank top 3 nationally. Mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 variable income for commission income with 24-month averaging baseline extended to 36-48 months for low-volume / high-value LMM M&A practices to capture full deal cycle plus continuity narrative documenting active engagements plus pipeline plus transaction track record. B3-3.2-01 self-employed for solo Florida business broker operating Schedule C / single-member PLLC with Form 1084 add-backs depreciation plus business use of home plus technology plus research plus marketing plus CE costs. B3-3.4-02 partnership / S-corp for boutique M&A firm equity partners with K-1 partnership distributions plus 2-year personal plus firm entity returns plus partnership agreement excerpt plus ownership percentage plus Form 1084 cash-flow analysis at firm entity level. S-corp election PLLC common for established business brokers splitting W-2 plus K-1 with Form 1084 at S-corp entity level. Retainer income separately tracked under B3-3.1-01 standard with 2-year history as more predictable component. Lehman scale commission documentation through engagement letter plus closing statement. Multi-source synthesis combining commission plus retainer plus K-1 plus spouse W-2. Conventional Jumbo for HNW LMM M&A advisors plus boutique partners. Bank Statement Non-QM. P&L Statement Non-QM. Asset-Depletion Non-QM useful between deal cycles. DSCR Non-QM. Cash-Out Refinance. Construction-to-Perm." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/business-advisors/business-broker/">
  <div class="bizbroker-scope" set:html={bizbrokerBody} />

<HomeReviews />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
.bizbroker-scope{
      color-scheme: light only;
      --ink: #0A0E1A;
      --ink-2: #1E2433;
      --ink-3: #2C3548;
      --ink-light: #4A5568;
      --ink-lighter: #6B7280;
      --paper: #FAFAF7;
      --paper-2: #F4F4EE;
      --paper-3: #EDEDE5;
      --white: #FFFFFF;
      --blue: #1845D6;
      --blue-deep: #0F2EA0;
      --blue-soft: #E8EEFF;
      --blue-tint: #F2F5FF;
      --gold: #B8860B;
      --rust: #8B2C2C;
      --border: #E5E5DE;
      --border-strong: #D4D4C8;
      --border-dark: #2C3548;
      --text-2xs: 0.6875rem; 
      --text-xs: 0.75rem;    
      --text-sm: 0.875rem;   
      --text-base: 1.0625rem;
      --text-md: 1.1875rem;  
      --text-lg: 1.375rem;   
      --text-xl: 1.625rem;   
      --text-2xl: 2rem;      
      --text-3xl: 2.75rem;   
      --text-4xl: 3.75rem;   
      --text-5xl: 5rem;      
      --s-1: 0.25rem;
      --s-2: 0.5rem;
      --s-3: 0.75rem;
      --s-4: 1rem;
      --s-5: 1.5rem;
      --s-6: 2rem;
      --s-7: 3rem;
      --s-8: 4rem;
      --s-9: 6rem;
      --s-10: 8rem;
      --s-11: 10rem;
      --serif: 'Fraunces', 'Iowan Old Style', Georgia, serif;
      --sans: 'IBM Plex Sans', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
      --mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'SF Mono', Menlo, monospace;
    }
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {.bizbroker-scope, .bizbroker-scope{
        background-color: #FAFAF7 !important;
        color: #0A0E1A !important;
        color-scheme: light only !important;
      }.bizbroker-scope *{
        forced-color-adjust: none;
      }
    }.bizbroker-scope, .bizbroker-scope *::before, .bizbroker-scope *::after{ box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }.bizbroker-scope{ scroll-behavior: smooth; -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; }.bizbroker-scope{
      font-family: var(--sans);
      font-size: var(--text-base);
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--ink);
      background: var(--paper);
      font-feature-settings: 'kern' 1, 'liga' 1, 'calt' 1;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
    }.bizbroker-scope img, .bizbroker-scope svg{ display: block; max-width: 100%; }.bizbroker-scope a{ color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }.bizbroker-scope button{ font: inherit; cursor: pointer; border: 0; background: none; }.bizbroker-scope .container{ max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--s-6); }.bizbroker-scope .container-narrow{ max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--s-6); }.bizbroker-scope .container-wide{ max-width: 1340px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--s-6); }.bizbroker-scope .eyebrow{
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: var(--text-xs);
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--blue);
      font-weight: 500;
      display: inline-block;
    }.bizbroker-scope .display-1{
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 4vw, 3rem);
      font-weight: 400;
      line-height: 1.0;
      letter-spacing: -0.025em;
      font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 30;
      color: var(--ink);
    }.bizbroker-scope .display-2{
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, var(--text-3xl));
      font-weight: 400;
      line-height: 1.05;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      font-variation-settings: "opsz" 100, "SOFT" 50;
      color: var(--ink);
    }.bizbroker-scope h2{
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, var(--text-2xl));
      font-weight: 450;
      line-height: 1.1;
      letter-spacing: -0.015em;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: var(--s-5);
      font-variation-settings: "opsz" 60, "SOFT" 50;
    }.bizbroker-scope h3{
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-size: var(--text-xl);
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1.25;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: var(--s-4);
      font-variation-settings: "opsz" 30;
    }.bizbroker-scope h4{
      font-family: var(--sans);
      font-size: var(--text-md);
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.3;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
      letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    }.bizbroker-scope p{ margin-bottom: var(--s-4); }.bizbroker-scope p:last-child{ margin-bottom: 0; }.bizbroker-scope p.lead{
      font-size: var(--text-lg);
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: var(--ink-2);
      font-weight: 350;
    }.bizbroker-scope p.lede{
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-size: var(--text-xl);
      line-height: 1.45;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-weight: 350;
      font-variation-settings: "opsz" 30;
    }.bizbroker-scope .body-text{ color: var(--ink-2); }.bizbroker-scope .text-muted{ color: var(--ink-lighter); }.bizbroker-scope .text-small{ font-size: var(--text-sm); }.bizbroker-scope .text-mono{ font-family: var(--mono); font-feature-settings: 'tnum' 1; }.bizbroker-scope strong, .bizbroker-scope b{ font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); }.bizbroker-scope em, .bizbroker-scope i{ font-style: italic; }.bizbroker-scope .nav{
